
= Spanish/Brazilian 15M activist and journalist

Twitter handle via @bernardosampa


=Bio=

Spanish journalist, activist and digital consultant who has worked for  newspapers and magazines such as La Vanguardia, El País, Expresso (Lisbon), 20  Minutos, Esquire, Der Tagesspiegel (Berlin) or National Geographic. He is the  CEO and Founder of Futura Media, a glocal innovation network around openness  settled in São Paulo (Brazil). Futura Media deals with open processes, links  between networks and territories and open source philosophy. Bernardo is involved  with global networks and movements as 15M-Indignados, Occupy or Movimento Social  das Culturas (Brazil) and researches about new hacktivism, commons, copyleft,  sharing economy and P2P philosophy. 

